d 'DUMMIFY': module to create indicator variables with automatic variable labels
d
d      dummify creates a set of indicator (0/1) variables from a
d categorical variable, one for each level, and    labels each one
d automatically in the form "variable label = value label". It also
d reports a compact summary    table listing each level, its value
d label, and the indicator created for it.  Essentially, it is a
d more	  convenient implementation of tabulate, generate(),
d producing indicators that carry meaningful variable	 labels
d rather than the bare stems that tabulate, generate() leaves
d behind.    varname must be numeric and contain only non-negative
d integer values. By default an indicator is created for    every
d level; base or base(#) designates one level as an omitted
d reference category. An indicator equals 1    where varname takes
d the corresponding value and 0 elsewhere, and is left missing
d wherever varname is	 missing. 
d
d KW: data management
d KW: indicator variables
d KW: variable labels
d
d Requires: Stata version 14 
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260612
d
d Author:  Gorkem Aksaray,  Trinity College Dublin
d Support: email aksarayg@@tcd.ie
d
f dummify.ado
f dummify.sthlp
